│ The issue is a miscompilation in `instcombine` where `shufflevector(select(C, A, B), D, M)` is incorrectly transformed into `select(C, shufflevector(A, D, M), shufflevector(B, D, M))`. │
│ This is unsafe when `D` contains concrete values that can replace `poison` values from `A` or `B`.                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The code performing this transformation is in `InstCombineVectorOps.cpp`, inside `visitShuffleVectorInst`. It currently allows this for any constant `D` (`RHS` in the code). I will     │
│ restrict this to only allow the transformation when `D` is `undef`, `poison`, or a zero constant. This prevents the incorrect "un-poisoning" of values.                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ patch -p1 <<'EOF'                                                                                                                                                                        │
